-- Barclays Capital Hires Michael Gapen, Antonio Garcia Pascual as Economists
-- Caroline Salas
-- 2010-07-08T16:13:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/barclays-capital-hires-michael-gapen-antonio-garcia-pascual-as-economists.html

          
          
             Barclays Capital, the investment
banking arm of Barclays Plc, named  Michael Gapen  and  Antonio Garcia Pascual  senior economists.  
 Gapen, 41, joined Barclays in New York as senior U.S.
economist and reports to  Dean Maki , chief U.S. economist,
Barclays said in a statement today. He was previously a section
chief for the Federal Reserve’s Board of Governors who was in
charge of monetary and financial markets analysis.  
 Garcia Pascual, 39, was hired as chief southern European
economist in London, and reports to  Julian Callow , chief
European economist, Barclays said. Before joining Barclays,
Garcia Pascual was a senior economist in the monetary and
capital markets group at the International Monetary Fund.  
 London-based Barclays is the U.K.’s third-largest  bank .  
